# arvo

Numeric primitives for hilavitkutin and consumers. Const-generic
fixed-point, float wrappers, composable traits, UFixed-based
aliases (`Uint5`..`Uint64`, `Int8`..`Int64`, cfg-gated `USize`) so
consumer code uses arvo types in every numeric position, never bare
primitives. `#![no_std]`, no alloc.
